The paper deals with domain generalization, which is a problem in machine learning and falls under the category of "Learning" (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on computer vision tasks, which suggests that it could also belong to "Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition" (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel approach to learning a feature representation that is useful for novel data and novel categories, which falls under the category of "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of natural language processing techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). Finally, the paper proposes a learning to learn approach, which falls under the category of "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE).
